EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 152300 UTC
SUNDAY EVENING A WEAK RIDGE IS POSITIONED ACROSS THE UK WITH AN ANTICYCLONIC
CENTRE 1030 CENTRED OVER DENMARK. A SECOND ANTICYCLONE 1034 LIES CENTRED
TO THE W OF THE AZORES. THESE CENTRES BOTH REMAINING SLOW MOV ON MONDAY AND
TUESDAY WITH THE DENMARK ANTICYCLONE SLWY DECLINING AND AS IT MOVS NE TOWARDS
FINLAND. MEANWHILE THE AZORES ANTICYCLONE CENTRE AMPLIFIES SLTLY. AN AREA
OF LOW PRESSURE IS EXP TO DEVELOP IN THE N ATLANTIC ON SUNDAY MOV NE ACROSS
NWERN PORTPATRICK SEA AREAS TO ARRIVE IN BAILEY 997 BY MIDDAY MONDAY. THIS
LOW THEN MOVS STEADILY THROUGH FAEROES AND AWAY INTO NORWEGIAN BASIN DURING
TUESDAY. RIDGE CONDITIONS RETURNING IN THE WAKE OF THIS LOW. GALES ARE NOT
CURRENTLY EXP ACROSS CULLERCOATS DURING THE PERIOD. HOWEVER STRG TO LOC
NEAR GALE WINDS ARE EXP AT TIMES PARTICULARLY ACROSS NW OF THE CULLERCOATS
REGION SUNDAY NIGHT INTO EARLY MONDAY AND ALSO PERHAPS LATE MONDAY NIGHT
